853  __IO uint32_t DINEP1MSK; /* dedicated EP mask 844h*/
854  uint32_t Reserved44[15]; /* Reserved 844-87Ch*/
855  __IO uint32_t DOUTEP1MSK; /* dedicated EP msk 884h*/
856 }
857 USB_OTG_DeviceTypeDef;
858 
859 
863 typedef struct
864 {
865  __IO uint32_t DIEPCTL; /* dev IN Endpoint Control Reg 900h + (ep_num * 20h) + 00h*/
866  uint32_t Reserved04; /* Reserved 900h + (ep_num * 20h) + 04h*/
867  __IO uint32_t DIEPINT; /* dev IN Endpoint Itr Reg 900h + (ep_num * 20h) + 08h*/
868  uint32_t Reserved0C; /* Reserved 900h + (ep_num * 20h) + 0Ch*/
869  __IO uint32_t DIEPTSIZ; /* IN Endpoint Txfer Size 900h + (ep_num * 20h) + 10h*/
870  __IO uint32_t DIEPDMA; /* IN Endpoint DMA Address Reg 900h + (ep_num * 20h) + 14h*/
871  __IO uint32_t DTXFSTS;/*IN Endpoint Tx FIFO Status Reg 900h + (ep_num * 20h) + 18h*/
872  uint32_t Reserved18; /* Reserved 900h+(ep_num*20h)+1Ch-900h+ (ep_num * 20h) + 1Ch*/
873 }

887  __IO uint32_t DOEPDMA; /* dev OUT Endpoint DMA Address B00h + (ep_num * 20h) + 14h*/

6527  Eight sequential Reads from this address (offset 0x28) will read all Wake-UpFrame Filter Registers. */
6528 /* Wake-UpFrame Filter Reg0 : Filter 0 Byte Mask
6529  Wake-UpFrame Filter Reg1 : Filter 1 Byte Mask
6530  Wake-UpFrame Filter Reg2 : Filter 2 Byte Mask
6531  Wake-UpFrame Filter Reg3 : Filter 3 Byte Mask
6532  Wake-UpFrame Filter Reg4 : RSVD - Filter3 Command - RSVD - Filter2 Command -
6533  RSVD - Filter1 Command - RSVD - Filter0 Command
6534  Wake-UpFrame Filter Re5 : Filter3 Offset - Filter2 Offset - Filter1 Offset - Filter0 Offset
